---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';
const all = (await getCollection('recipes')).filter(r => !r.data.draft);
---
<BaseLayout title="About — FlutterCook">
  <main class="wrap">
    <article class="article">
      <div class="crumb"><a href="/">FlutterCook</a> / about</div>
      <h1 class="serif">A cookbook for <i>open-source</i> Flutter.</h1>
      <div class="prose">
        <p>FlutterCook is a growing library of {all.length} hands-on recipes for the best open-source Flutter and Dart projects — libraries, UI components, state management, animation, backend, and AI. Every recipe is chosen from live GitHub trend data and pub.dev, so the list reflects what the community is actually building with right now.</p>
        <h2 class="serif">How recipes are <i>chosen</i></h2>
        <p>We scan hundreds of Flutter/Dart repositories, rank them by stars weighted for recent activity, layer in editorial "must-know" picks and YouTube demand signals, then write a focused guide for each. The <a href="/trends">live trends page</a> shows the raw leaderboard, refreshed on every visit.</p>
        <h2 class="serif">Built in the <i>open</i></h2>
        <p>Source and demos live at <a href="https://github.com/fluttercook" target="_blank" rel="noopener">github.com/fluttercook</a>. This site is built with <a href="https://astro.build" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Astro</a> and deployed to GitHub Pages; a companion edition is published at <a href="https://flutter9.blogspot.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">flutter9.blogspot.com</a>.</p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
